Problem:
public class WeatherSystem {
  private boolean isRaining;
  private int temperature;
  public WeatherSystem(boolean rain, int temp) {
    isRaining = rain;
    temperature = temp;
  }
  public void adjustWeather() {
    if (temperature > 30) {
      isRaining = false;
    } else if (temperature < 20) {
      isRaining = true;
    }
  }
  public boolean willItRain() {
    return isRaining;
  }
  public void increaseTemperature(int increment) {
    temperature += increment;
    adjustWeather();
  }
  public String getWeatherStatus() {
    if (isRaining) {
      return "Rainy";
    } else {
      return "Sunny";
    }
  }
}",

If the temperature is increased by 20 degrees from 15 degrees, will the system end up predicting sunny weather?
